<BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59249">Teldi's gear</a>~~~<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=251998">Voliciti's gear</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teldivagrimleux>Teldiva GrimLeux</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.sc.rr.com/kimmisc/telseye.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/27/02 6:53:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gadine>Gadine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.primecolorphoto.com/images/realm%20powers/rplights/.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(10/27/02 7:17:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far is safe to explore solo?</span><hr size=1> PoJ and PoT are fine to zone into, though there are some rats in PoJ.  They conned green to me at 61.  PoJ has at least one quest for a full group that involves prisoners and a trial, with waves of fighting.  Apparently end result if the group is successful is a flag to enable entrance into another pop zone.<br>
<br>
PoT has quests and the zone in for PoD, PoI, and PoJ which I believe are the only zones that can be entered without questing.<br>
<br>
Just do the usual thing, invis up before entering, and proceed cautiously, con'ing everything that comes near.  There are quad kiters in PoD which adds to the difficulty there.  PoI has a very fast respawn rate with mobs that hit very hard, but don't have a tremendous amount of HP.  <br>
<br>
We believe that each of the zones has a graveyard near zone in where your corpse will appear 10 minutes after death, making CR much easier. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.realmpowers.net"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.technosapien.net/rp-sign/Gadine-sign.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=canelin@themagicianstower>Canelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 1:15:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Rats</span><hr size=1> I zoned into PoJ the other night and saw the rats, although I didn't con them.  Just ran away like a frightend girl.<br>
<br>
Are these things likely to be a source of exp for us lower levels (I'm 54), without entering deep into the plane itself?<br>
<br>
