<br>
And if you want to explore nightmare, part of the zone isn't KoS to the enchanter Imp illusion spell(Tricksters Augmentation) so get someone to cast that on you and go to town.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teldivagrimleux>Teldiva GrimLeux</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.sc.rr.com/kimmisc/telseye.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1120<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 5:40:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.sc.rr.com/kimmisc/persicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rats</span><hr size=1> Quad kiting in the planes?  Hmmmm, so there are mobs up there that are soloable!? <p><img src=http://home.sc.rr.com/kimmisc/dedollsig.jpg>
<BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59249">Teldi's gear</a>~~~<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=251998">Voliciti's gear</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1321<br> <font color=#333333>(10/28/02 6:23:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How far is safe to explore solo?</span><hr size=1> Teldiva,<br>
<br>
If you mean &quot;can I possibly kill a mob solo&quot; then yes, but not very effeciently.  Plan on doing a lot of chain casting.<br>
<br>
From what I've seen so far- (1) PoP mobs have very high DPS, and (2) PoP mobs have resonably low hp for their level.<br>
<br>
This is why the quad-kiters are getting away with it, they don't get hit.  Just like a druid who roots and DoTs the cobalt drakes in CS never worry about the AE dmg proc.  If you don't get hit, you're fine.<br>
<br>
However, for a magician, going up against mobs who hit for 250+ damage is pretty difficult.  Some of those mobs were tearing through my epic pets without blinking.  Had a 61 druid and 61 wizard with me and the druid had to use his CH spell at least once per battle, sometimes twice.  We lost about 4 epics at the beginning because they were dying so fast.  Took the druid a few times to get the timing down on when to cast his 10 sec. heal.<br>
<br>
We added a 59 paladin and another magician and suddenly the kills were coming quite fast, then a 60 shaman joined in for slows and suddenly what was a complete mana drain was quite doable.<br>
<br>
Try to explore if you want, as they said the graveyard is right by zone in to get your corpse if it goes bad <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
